			>
			<DIV>Ironically, the druid boards have a very similiar thread.&nbsp; this is a universal caster issue - when you die it takes&nbsp;a LONG time to get back to full mana even with all the regen possibilities: FT20 MC3, C6, SA, Oakskin/AotP, Choru of Life and click effect.&nbsp; However, in my experience I do not need to be full mana in order to continue in a group setting.&nbsp; I only NEED about 30% and most casters I know can usually contribute what they need to (DPS, Slow, Mez) at 10% to 20%.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As a cleric who does RDS and Pet each fight and melee's so I use Yaulp 7 all the time, if I die I get rezzed I rebuff and wait until I hit 30% to 40% mana then I am ready to go.&nbsp; All I do is moderate how and what I cast: if MoB is resistsed I don't recast, I do not cast my pet on all mobs, and I do not nuke).&nbsp; Slowly but surely (unless something bad happens again) I regen mana faster than I use it and I am at 80% to 90% again.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This all being said, I would not mind seeing a mana regen model like the health regen model where the longer you sit the more regen you get.</DIV>	
