<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&message.id=10686#M10686">8</a> of 44
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1083 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Griffin131 wrote:<BR>I didnt count clickies on purpose, but I'll go with +4 since all the 11k+ clerics I looked at have at least that.<BR><BR>90*148=13320 mana. Is 5 minutes a reasonable downtime? It's not like you have to be 100% mana to heal for trash.<BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>In our guild, with 14 level 70 Clerics, only 1 or 2&nbsp;has the clicky. And I did not consider SA because it is a much less common spell in groups than C6 is. But even at the theoretical max of 96 per tick that was stated above, my 11.4 k buffed&nbsp;mana pool needs over 12 minutes.</P>
<P>But that is not really the issue. For me the two main issues are:</P>
<P>1. All high end casters have a mana regen that is too slow. It was never scaled up significantly - nor properly -&nbsp;from the old 3 year old mana pools. As far as I know, the only thing casters and hybrids&nbsp;got was the extra 3 FT AA.</P>
<P>2. Hundreds of times, on raids and groups, I have seen the old familiar phrase... "waiting on Cleric mana...". On 98% of all raids it is cleric mana that causes the long pauses. I almost never see raids or groups hold up for any other reason. And, I don't know how widespread or significant this is, but I was told in one group that they preferred a shammy healer because they could regen mana for heals so much faster and not hold up the group.</P>
<P>This is an EQ1 problem. I have played several other games, and EQ1 has by FAR the slowest mana (or equivalent) regen. And that would include Stamina regen for melee's. None of the regens, except for HP where you now get a boost while sitting, was ever upgraded to any extent to account for the much larger than original pools.</P>
<P>And I wonder why the sitting HP regen was not extended to mana and stamina?<BR></P>
<DIV></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							70 Cleric (<a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/character_profile.vm?characterId=571230694339">The Pink Elf</a>) (854AA)<br>60 <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/character_profile.vm?characterId=571230973715">Warrior</a><br>70 <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/character_profile.vm?characterId=571231102724">Enchanter</a> (73 AA)<br>28 <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/character_profile.vm?characterId=571231473446">Ranger</a> fun gimp<br><br>Viking Alliance (Stromm)
