		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Thaere wrote:<BR>
<DIV>Ironically, the druid boards have a very similiar thread.&nbsp; this is a universal caster issue - when you die it takes&nbsp;a LONG time to get back to full mana even with all the regen possibilities: FT20 MC3, C6, SA, Oakskin/AotP, Choru of Life and click effect.&nbsp; However, in my experience I do not need to be full mana in order to continue in a group setting.<BR>
<HR>
</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>The real holdups come after a wipe, especially for buffing classes. First it takes me 5-10 minutes to get enough mana to cast all the buffs, then another 10-15 minutes to get back to FM or something close. So it can easily be a 15-25 minute downtime just for mana regen.</P>
<P>And I realize it is a caster-wide (and probably bard also) issue. But this issue has been around now for over 6 months, and has never been addressed since the cryptic "we are looking into it" message early last summer.</P>
<P>I don't know what the best way to boost mana (and probably stam) regen would be that would be fair to all, but it does not seem to me that a couple of simple temporary fixes would be all that difficult, such as increasing sitting regen, and perhaps a +4% boost per level&nbsp;for 60+.</P>
<P>But things will only get worse. By the next expansion, with the mudflation and all, I can see 20 minute downtimes in a year if the issue is not addressed.<BR></P>
<DIV></DIV><p>Message Edited by Laiina on <span class=date_text>12-07-2005</span> <span class=time_text>09:37 PM</span>
