<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&message.id=10693#M10693">10</a> of 44
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1064 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			I'm sure SOE is very well aware of the Endurance/Mana regen issues, and they have given more comments on it than just "We're looking into it." The biggest issue with the regen issues they mentionned is that currently EQ does not have a "Combat state" so they can easily tell if a person/group/raid is in a combat situation (where they would want the current regen rates, or something like that) vs a non-combat situation (where they would want a sped up regen rate). This is what lets EQII have its faster regen rates BTW.<br><br>Considering this is one of the most fundamental basics of the game, changing this system is not something they would take lightly.<br><br>It would be nice to have a bit more of an update on it, but SOE usually (and rightfully so) doesn't say what they are doing until it is about to hit test. This gives them more freedom to experiment and figure out "Ok this solution isn't going to work," without having the selective memory of the player base screaming "You said it would be going to test soon! Why isn't it released yet!"
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Saroc, L70 Dwarf Cleric; Member of Heroes 
Trilium, L52 Druid
Taeolas, L39 Ranger

Luclin server.
