			>
			<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr>
<P>Laiina wrote:</P>
<P>The real holdups come after a wipe, especially for buffing classes. First it takes me 5-10 minutes to get enough mana to cast all the buffs,<STRONG> </STRONG></P>
<P><STRONG></STRONG></P>
<HR>

<P></P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>You are correct that when a wipe occurs you watch that mana bar creep up and as soon as you are able you cast a buff and this typically takes about 5 to 10 minutes.</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr>
<P></P>
<HR>

<P></P>
<P>Laiina wrote:</P>
<P>then another 10-15 minutes to get back to FM or something close. So it can easily be a 15-25 minute downtime just for mana regen.</P>
<P></P>
<HR>

<P></P></BLOCKQUOTE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr>
<DIV>However, do you <STRONG><EM><U>REALLY ABSOLUTELY POSSITIVELY NEED </U></EM></STRONG>full mana "or something close" to start pulls again in a group though?&nbsp; in my experience the answer is an absolute <STRONG><EM><U>NO!</U></EM></STRONG>&nbsp; Even way back when I was in BoT and HoH, and only had a 5.5k man pool, I only <STRONG><EM><U>NEEDED</U></EM></STRONG> about 40% mana in order for the group to start pulling again and for DPS casters it's even less.&nbsp; The casters I've known and grouped with who fill key roles (slower, CC, snare, etc) have usually said "good to go" when they were at 20% mana.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Even back in PoP I typically regened faster than I used my mana (back then I only ahd FT7 + MC3 + KEI) so all&nbsp;I needed was 30% to 40% becaue I knew (and still know) that in most cases I will be at 95% mana soon enough. (and before someone says, " why not go at 5% mana then?" my answer is because I'm not that stupid - group gets&nbsp;a bad pull after a wipe and we're dead again if I say good to go at only 5% mana.&nbsp; at least at 30% I can cast several fast heals and not be oom).</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It's called mana management and obviously some do it better than others.&nbsp; If you <STRONG><EM><U>REALLY ABSOLUTELY POSSITIVELY NEED </U></EM></STRONG>full mana to start pulls again in a group there is something very wrong with your style of casting or the group makeup.&nbsp; If it's the latter there is not much you can do except change groups.&nbsp; If it's the former, I highly recommend you rethink what you are casting and how much you are casting it.</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Saroc_Luclin wrote:<BR>I'm sure SOE is very well aware of the Endurance/Mana regen issues, and they have given more comments on it than just "We're looking into it." The biggest issue with the regen issues they mentionned is that currently EQ does not have a "Combat state" so they can easily tell if a person/group/raid is in a combat situation (where they would want the current regen rates, or something like that) vs a non-combat situation (where they would want a sped up regen rate). This is what lets EQII have its faster regen rates BTW.<BR><BR>Considering this is one of the most fundamental basics of the game, changing this system is not something they would take lightly.<BR><BR>It would be nice to have a bit more of an update on it, but SOE usually (and rightfully so) doesn't say what they are doing until it is about to hit test. This gives them more freedom to experiment and figure out "Ok this solution isn't going to work," without having the selective memory of the player base screaming "You said it would be going to test soon! Why isn't it released yet!"<BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>But wait a second - did they not recently (long time ago actually), change the health regen mechanic?&nbsp; They made health regen increase incrementally the longer you sat and did nothing.&nbsp; If they can do that for health regen why not mana or endurance regen?&nbsp; I would think this would be an easy implement and would quiet some of this complaining down.	
