<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&message.id=10737#M10737">18</a> of 44
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 896 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			I believe the desire is to have that state be Group and/or Raid wide, so that if anyone in group has aggro, the bonuses don't apply, ditto for raid. <br><br>The Aggro dumping classes are a thorn in the plans too. I doubt the Dev's want the necro's 'simply' raid disbanding, FDing during an encounter and medding to full faster than anyone else. (Or Monk's doing the same for endurance). So some way has to be developed to set up that 'non combat' state, while at the same time not wrecking in game concepts like FD, Bard Fade, monk FDing, etc. Nor even a cleric going OOM, camping, logging back in and staying out of raid till he's medded to full. <br><br>Pulling would be an issue as well. Ideally you would want the faster regen while someone was out pulling, but as soon as that person got aggro, everyone loses that regen rate. You could see people disbanding the puller from the group, and reinviting while the pull is inc.<br><br>You'll notice that with Chest rewards, if you have aggro (from even a trap annoyingly), you can't loot. But if someone hasn't gotten aggro in your group, they can loot the chest. Which means that the Aggro check code is not Groupwide.
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Saroc, L70 Dwarf Cleric; Member of Heroes 
Trilium, L52 Druid
Taeolas, L39 Ranger

Luclin server.
							</div>
								
